# Sidebar Nested Sub-Navigation Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Upgrade the existing Sidebar navigation system in the Smart HR Client to support **nested / expandable navigation** aligned with the Case-Centric Information Architecture. The implementation will include role-based access control (RBAC), RTL/LTR compatibility, persisted expand/collapse states, and deep linking for sub-tabs.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Navigation Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [client/src/components/layout/_nav.ts](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/_nav.ts)
- Extend the [NavItem](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/_nav.ts#21-28) interface to support an optional `children` array (sub-items).
- Add all sub-items specified in the IA requirements to their respective parent nodes.
- Use deep links (e.g., `?tab=admin` or `?view=performance`) for sub-items that correspond to tabs within existing pages.
- Apply `rolesAllowed` to sub-items to respect RBAC gating.
- Update [filterNavByRole](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/_nav.ts#132-145) to recursively or selectively filter out sub-items, and hide parent sections if they have no visible sub-items left.

### 2. Sidebar Component UI and Interaction
#### [MODIFY] [client/src/components/layout/DashboardLayout.tsx](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/DashboardLayout.tsx)
- Implement local state for tracking expanded/collapsed parent sections.
- Integrate `localStorage` to persist the expanded state (`sidebar_expanded_sections_v1`).
- Add auto-expansion logic based on the `location.pathname` upon mount or path changes.
- Update the [NavContent](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/components/layout/DashboardLayout.tsx#36-74) rendering logic to display parent items with a toggleable chevron icon.
- Render sub-items iteratively beneath the parent when expanded, ensuring indentation and styling handles RTL/LTR properly.
- Update mobile UX to close the sidebar `Sheet` when a sub-item is navigated.

### 3. Locale Updates
#### [MODIFY] [client/src/locales/ar.json](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/locales/ar.json) & [en.json](file:///d:/%D9%85%D8%B4%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B9/14-2-2026/2026-2-13/smart_performance_system/client/src/locales/en.json)
- Add new i18n keys for all the newly introduced sub-items to maintain full Arabic RTL support and English translation parity.

### 4. Documentation
#### [NEW] `docs/sidebar-nested-navigation.md`
- Create documentation outlining the behavior (expand/collapse, persistence), IA mapping, deep-link conventions, and the affected files.

## User Review Required
None specifically, but RBAC and Deep Links mapping will be closely matched to existing patterns.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run TS build to ensure interface extensions do not break existing code.

### Manual Verification
- **AT-Sidebar-01:** Navigate the sidebar and check expand/collapse behavior on main items.
- **AT-Sidebar-02:** Click sub-items and ensure they navigate correctly to existing routes or deep links.
- **AT-Sidebar-03:** Reload the page to confirm that the expanded/collapsed state persists.
- **AT-Sidebar-04:** Check that the current route's parent section auto-expands on initial load.
- **AT-RBAC-01:** Log in with different mock roles (if possible) or review filtering logic to ensure forbidden items are hidden.
- **AT-RTL-01:** Switch direction (RTL/LTR) to confirm alignment, indentation, and chevron direction remain proper.
